('3d07285a-ee36-48e2-b66d-3780a5b29892', '15092025018', 'draft', '<ul><li><strong>5 NIGHT STAY AT </strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36);\">SAVOY CREST HOTEL </strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">WITH BREAKFAST</strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36);\">.</strong></li><li><strong>2 NIGHT STAY AT CROWN PLAZA ABU DHABHI-YASH ISLAND </strong><strong style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">WITH BREAKFAST</strong><strong>. </strong></li><li><strong>ALL SIGHT SEEN AS PER ITINERARY.</strong></li></ul>', '<ul><li><strong>Tourism Dirham if not mentioned in the inclusions&nbsp;.</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(32, 31, 30);\">OTB is not included in the package. (It depends upon the airline).</strong></li><li><strong>Any expense of personal nature not mentioned in the inclusions&nbsp;.</strong></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(32, 31, 30);\">Tips / Gratuities</strong></li></ul>', '<h2><strong>DAY 1 :</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Airport Transfer</strong>&nbsp;from DUBAI INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT T1/T2/T3</li><li><strong>Marina Dhow Cruise Dinner - Standard&nbsp;</strong>:&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(13, 13, 13);\">A relaxing cruise with the view of sky scrapers of Dubai Marina with lavish buffet dinner and entertainment show on board.</span></li><li><strong>Nights Stay in </strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36);\">Savoy Crest Hotel Apartments</strong></li></ul><h2><strong style=\"color: rgb(13, 13, 13);\">DAY 2 :</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Dubai Half Day City Tour - 5 Hour (Private)</strong>&nbsp;: Experience panoramic half day city tour of Dubai and enjoy Old and New Dubai sightseeing.</li><li><strong>Monorail Ticket&nbsp;</strong>:&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(13, 13, 13);\">The most iconic way to navigate across the Palm Jumeirah. It is not a mere form of transportation; it\'s an experiential journey.</span></li><li><strong>Standard Dubai Desert Safari 4X4 with Camel Ride, BBQ Dinner, Belly Dance show (Private)</strong>&nbsp;: Enjoy Magical &amp; Memorable Evening with Dune Bashing, BBQ Dinner and Entertainment Shows.</li><li><strong>Nights Stay in </strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36);\">Savoy Crest Hotel Apartments</strong></li></ul><h2><strong>DAY 3 : </strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Dubai Frame&nbsp;</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>:&nbsp;</strong>An architectural landmark which holds the record for the largest frame in the world</li><li><strong>At the top burj khalifa - 124th floor Non-Prime&nbsp;</strong>: The tallest structure and building in the world:&nbsp;&nbsp;And enjoy shopping at Dubai Mall; But not to miss the fascinating Fountain Show.</li><li><strong>Nights Stay in </strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36);\">Savoy Crest Hotel Apartments</strong></li></ul><h2><strong>DAY 4 :</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>The View at the Palm Non-prime&nbsp;</strong>: Enjoy incomparable views of one of Dubai’s most talked about landmarks at The View at The Palm.</li><li><strong>Atlantis Aquaventure water park + Lost chamber&nbsp;</strong>: World\'s largest waterpark promises a world of excitement to make you feel #DifferentInWater in more ways than one . Atlantis-themed aquarium with underwater halls &amp; tunnels housing marine life, plus feeding sessions.</li><li><strong>Nights Stay in </strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36);\">Savoy Crest Hotel Apartments</strong></li></ul><h2><strong>DAY 5:</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Museum of the Future&nbsp;</strong>: The Museum of the Future is an exhibition space for innovative and futuristic ideologies, services, and products&nbsp;<strong style=\"color: rgb(192, 57, 43);\"><em>(Subject to availability at time of booking)</em></strong></li><li><strong>Miracle Garden&nbsp;</strong>:&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(13, 13, 13);\">World\'s largest natural flower garden, featuring over 50 million flowers and 250 million plants.&nbsp;</span></li><li><strong>Global Village&nbsp;</strong>:&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(13, 13, 13);\">World\'s largest tourism, leisure, shopping and entertainment project by combining cultures of 90 countries</span></li><li><strong>Nights Stay in </strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36);\">Savoy Crest Hotel Apartments</strong></li></ul><h2><strong>DAY 6 :</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Full Day Abu Dhabi City Tour - 10 Hour (Private)</strong>&nbsp;: Discover the rich heritage and modern marvels of the UAE’s capital with our immersive Abu Dhabi City Tour &amp; drop to Abu Dhabi Hotel.</li><li><strong>Nights Stay in </strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36);\">Crowne Plaza Abu Dhabi - Yas Island</strong></li></ul><h2><strong>DAY 7 :</strong></h2><ul><li><strong>Day at Yas Island</strong></li><li>&nbsp;<strong>Nights Stay in </strong><strong style=\"color: rgb(36, 36, 36);\">Crowne Plaza Abu Dhabi - Yas Island</strong></li></ul><h2><strong>DAY 8 :</strong></h2><ul><li>CHECK OUT FROM THE HOTEL</li><li><strong>Airport Transfer</strong>&nbsp;to DUBAI INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT T1/T2/T3</li><li>All Tours and Transfers are based on&nbsp;<strong>PVT basis&nbsp;</strong></li></ul>', '<h2><strong style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 0);\">VISA CHARGES 7500/- INR PER PERSON</strong></h2><p><br></p><h2>VISA DOCCUMENT LIST :</h2><ul><li><strong>Hotel Booking</strong></li><li><strong>Passport</strong></li><li><strong>Passport Back</strong></li><li><strong>Round Trip Flight Ticket</strong></li><li><strong>Traveler Photo</strong></li><li><strong>Pan Card</strong></li></ul>', '{\"1758025275125\":{\"ratePerPerson\":\"45361\",\"remarks\":\"\",\"rows\":[{\"key\":\"1758025276077\",\"travelDate\":\"2025-10-18\",\"flightNo\":\"AL 2658\",\"departure\":\"RAJKOT \",\"arrival\":\"MUMBAI\",\"departureTime\":\"08:40\",\"arrivalTime\":\"10:10\",\"passenger\":\"3\",\"baggage\":\"25\"},{\"key\":\"1758025307969\",\"travelDate\":\"2025-10-18\",\"flightNo\":\"AL 2201\",\"departure\":\"MUMBAI \",\"arrival\":\"DUBAI\",\"departureTime\":\"16:25\",\"arrivalTime\":\"18:15\",\"passenger\":\"3\",\"baggage\":\"25\"},{\"key\":\"1758025309185\",\"travelDate\":\"2025-10-25\",\"flightNo\":\"AL 920\",\"departure\":\"DUBAI \",\"arrival\":\"MUMBAI\",\"departureTime\":\"18:55\",\"arrivalTime\":\"23:50\",\"passenger\":\"3\",\"baggage\":\"25\"},{\"key\":\"1758025310199\",\"travelDate\":\"2025-10-26\",\"flightNo\":\"AL 659\",\"departure\":\"MUMBAI \",\"arrival\":\"RAJKOT\",\"departureTime\":\"06:35\",\"arrivalTime\":\"07:55\",\"passenger\":\"3\",\"baggage\":\"25\"}]}}', 'Continental Plan (CP)', '2025-09-16 07:41:00', '2025-09-16 13:22:13', 'd75e5de4-524b-4425-8802-7cfeee6834b0', '0d88fbdc-1552-4281-a5de-206a35a3f42d', '15092025018_Q02', NULL, '{\"1758006740728\":{\"adults\":\"1193\",\"extraAdults\":\"\",\"childWithBed\":\"\",\"childWithoutBed\":\"\",\"childsBelow5\":\"\",\"remarks\":\"PROVIDED RATES ARE BASE ON USD.\",\"rows\":[{\"key\":\"1758006742309\",\"hotelName\":\"Savoy Crest Hotel Apartments \",\"destination\":\"DUBAI\",\"checkIn\":\"2025-09-17\",\"checkOut\":\"2025-09-22\",\"roomCategory\":\"STUDIO ROOM\",\"noOfRooms\":\"1\"},{\"key\":\"1758006824139\",\"hotelName\":\"Crowne Plaza Abu Dhabi\",\"destination\":\"ABU DHABI \",\"checkIn\":\"2025-09-22\",\"checkOut\":\"2025-09-24\",\"roomCategory\":\"STANDERD ROOM \",\"noOfRooms\":\"1\"}]}}');
INSERT INTO `quotations` (`id`, `enquiryNo`, `status`, `inclusions`, `exclusions`, `itinerary`, `visaExclusions`, `flightDetails`, `mealPlan`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `leadId`, `userId`, `quotationNo`, `internalRemark`, `accommodationDetails`) VALUES
('43b95a3e-b857-441b-a348-11ac9ebed264', '30122025034', 'draft', '<ul><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Rooms on twin/triple sharing basis. Daily Breakfast. </span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Exclusive a/c private vehicle at disposal for transfers &amp; sightseeing as per itinerary. </span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Same Vehicle and Driver throughout the Tour. </span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Service of an experienced driver for 12 Hours per day up to maximum 08:00 PM. </span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Parking, Toll taxes, Drivers Allowance etc.</span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">If travelling to Kaziranga National Park&nbsp;01 Elephant safari (Subject to Availability) &amp; 01 Jeep safari.</span></li><li class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">If travelling to Arunachal Pradesh - Inner Line Permit.</span></li></ul>', '<ul><li><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Room Heater Charges. </span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Personal Expenses such as Laundry, telephone, tips, gratuity, Mineral/soft/hard drinks. Additional sightseeing or extra usage of vehicle, other than those mentioned in the itinerary. Camera fees, Guide / tour escort charges &amp; Entrance Fees.</span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Any cost arising due to natural calamities like, landslides, road&nbsp;blockage, political disturbances, etc (to be borne by the client, which is directly payable on the spot). </span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Any increase in taxes or fuel price, leading to increase in cost on surface transportation &amp; land arrangements, which may come into effect prior to departure. </span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">GST</span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Insurance</span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Anything which is not include in the inclusion.</span></li></ul>', '<p><strong>Day 1: 04-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Guwahati - Shillong (100 KM 3 HRS)</strong></p><p>&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Welcome to Awesome Assam! Our representative will be waiting to greet and assist you at the airport or railway station. Get ready for a memorable road trip of a lifetime as we head towards Shillong, often referred to as the Scotland of the East. Along the way, we will stop at the majestic Umium Lake (Barapani), where you can also enjoy optional water sports activities. Upon reaching Shillong, check in at your hotel. In the evening, you can explore the bustling Police Bazaar, the largest local market in the area. Enjoy your overnight stay in Shillong.</span></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Transfer(s):&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Urbania 10 Seats(10 Seater)</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Day 2: 05-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Shillong - Cherrapunji - Shillong (65 KM 1.5 Hrs Per Way)</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Wake up early today to immerse yourself in the mesmerizing mornings of Shillong. After an early breakfast, embark on a drive to Cherrapunji, renowned as the wettest place in the world. Explore various attractions including the Garden of Caves, Eco Park (closed on Wednesdays), Dainthlen Falls, Nohkalikai Falls, Nohsngithiang Falls (Seven Sisters Falls), Mawsmai Cave, and Thangkharang Park (closed on Wednesdays).</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">In the evening, return to Shillong and visit Elephanta Falls (closed on Sundays) and Shillong Peak (closed on Wednesdays) to witness breathtaking views. Conclude the day with a comfortable overnight stay in Shillong.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Day 3: 06-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Shillong - Dawki - Mawlynnong Village - Shillong (90 KM 2 Hrs Per Way)</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">After breakfast, journey to Mawlynnong Village, recognized as the cleanest village in India. This charming and vibrant village is celebrated for its immaculate surroundings. Located 90 kilometers from Shillong, Mawlynnong offers various attractions such as the Living Root Bridge and a peculiar natural phenomenon where a boulder balances on another rock. Next, proceed to Dawki, situated along the Indo-Bangladesh border. Here, you can partake in boating activities in the crystal-clear waters of the Umgnot River. In the evening, return to Shillong for an overnight stay.</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><strong>Day 4: 07-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Shillong - Kaziranga National Park (280 KM 6 Hrs)</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Following breakfast, we\'ll proceed to Kaziranga National Park, renowned as the habitat of the One-Horn Indian Rhinoceros. Upon arrival, check in at your chosen accommodation, whether it be a hotel, lodge, or resort. In the evening, you have the option to visit Orchid Park and explore the nearby Tea Plantations. Enjoy a comfortable overnight stay at Kaziranga National Park.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Day 5: 08-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Kaziranga National Park</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">In the early hours of the morning, we\'ll embark on a unique adventure, exploring Kaziranga National Park atop majestic elephants. This sanctuary is not only home to the endangered One-Horned Indian Rhinoceros but also shelters a significant portion of the world\'s genetically pure Wild Water Buffaloes, over 1000 Wild Elephants, and quite possibly the densest population of Royal Bengal Tigers in any habitat. Kaziranga National Park is a haven for bird enthusiasts, boasting a staggering 500 species of birds. Among them, the Crested Serpent Eagle, Palla&amp;rsquos Fishing Eagle, Greyheaded Fishing Eagle, Swamp Partridge, Bar-headed Goose, Whistling Teal, Bengal Florican, various Storks, Herons, and Pelicans grace the skies and waters.</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">After our morning expedition, we\'ll return to the resort for a hearty breakfast. In the afternoon, we\'ll set out on a thrilling jeep safari, immersing ourselves further in the wilderness. As evening descends, we\'ll return to the comfort of our hotel for a relaxing evening. Our overnight stay promises an unforgettable experience amidst the natural wonders of Kaziranga National Park.</span></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Sightseeing(s):&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Elephant Safari (SIC), Jeep Safari (SIC)</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Day 6: 09-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Kaziranga National Park - Dirang (260 Km 6 to 7 Hrs)</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Depart early in the morning for Dirang. Along the way, make a stop at the Orchid Research Centre Tipi, an orchidarium boasting around 10,000 orchid plants from various genera and species. Arunachal Pradesh is known to have the largest range of orchids in the country. As you continue your drive, ensure your cameras are ready to capture the beautiful waterfalls and breathtaking views along the route. During the journey, you\'ll also visit Nag Mandir.</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Upon arrival in Dirang, check in to your hotel. After lunch, explore the regional apple nursery, kiwi farm, hot water spring, Sangti Valley, and Dzong Fort. Conclude the day with an overnight stay in Dirang.</span></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Sightseeing(s):&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Inner Line Permit (SIC)</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Day 7: 10-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Dirang - Tawang (140 Km 6 Hrs)</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Following breakfast, we\'ll proceed to Tawang. Along the way, we\'ll stop to visit the War Cemetery. Our journey will continue, leading us to the majestic Sela Pass, situated at an elevation of 4170 meters (13700 feet). Renowned for its high altitude lakes and breathtaking scenery, the pass offers a picturesque vista. Continuing our drive, we\'ll arrive at the Jaswant Garh War Memorial, a tribute to the valiant Indian soldier Jaswant Singh Rawat.</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Later, we\'ll visit the enchanting Nuranang Falls, also known as Jang Falls. Upon reaching Tawang, we\'ll check in to our hotel for an overnight stay, embracing the tranquility of this picturesque destination.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Day 8: 11-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Tawang Local Or Bumla Pass</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">After breakfast, you have two options for the day. The first option is to visit Bum La Pass (Indo-China Border), Sangestar Lake (Madhuri Lake), and Pangateng Tso Lake (P.Tso Lake). Please note that you will need to obtain a permit from the DC office in Tawang by yourself for visiting Bum La Pass. Additionally, you will need to hire a local taxi in Tawang for these visits, as our vehicles are not permitted. The cost for the taxi will be on a direct payment basis.</span></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">Alternatively, you can choose to visit Tawang Monastery (Namgey Lhatse), Singsor Ani Gompa, and Tawang War Memorial. Please note that covering all these places in a day may not be feasible if you opt for the first option of visiting Bum La Pass and Madhuri Lake. In the evening, return to the hotel for an overnight stay in Tawang.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Day 9: 12-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Tawang - Bomdila (190 KM 7-8 HRS)</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">After breakfast, proceed to Bomdila. Upon arrival, check in at the hotel. Visit Bomdila Monastery and Bomdila View Point, which offers breathtaking panoramic views of the Himalayan landscapes and snow-clad ranges. In the evening, you may explore the local market. Overnight stay in Bomdila.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Day 10: 13-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Bomdila - Guwahati (335 KM 6 - 7 HRS)</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">After breakfast, proceed to Guwahati and check in at your hotel. In the evening, you have the option to enjoy a River Cruise on the majestic River Brahmaputra (Payment directly to the operator). You can also explore the local market, renowned for Assam\'s specialties such as Assam Silk, especially Golden Muga Silk, Assam Tea, Bamboo, and Cane Products. Overnight stay in Guwahati.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Day 11: 14-Mar-26</strong></p><p><strong>Guwahati Departure</strong></p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><span style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\">After breakfast, we\'ll check out from the hotel. If time permits, we can embark on a tour of the Kamakhya Temple and other temples in Guwahati, including the Purva Tirupati Shri Balaji Temple, Sukreswar Temple, Navagraha Temple, Umananda Temple on Peacock Island, which is the smallest inhabited river island in the world. Additionally, we can explore the Assam State Museum, Dighali Pukhuri (Lake), State Zoo cum Botanical Garden, Planetarium, and the Assam State Emporiums. With cherished memories, we\'ll proceed to Guwahati airport/railway station for our onward journey.</span></p>', '<p><br></p>', '{}', 'Modified American Plan (MAP)', '2025-12-30 13:11:43', '2025-12-31 07:28:35', NULL, '0cae09bb-571c-4816-bf1b-bab379e7a682', '30122025034_Q01', NULL, '{\"1767165247751\":{\"adults\":\"53500\",\"extraAdults\":\"\",\"childWithBed\":\"\",\"childWithoutBed\":\"\",\"childsBelow5\":\"\",\"remarks\":\"Rates are in INR \",\"rows\":[{\"key\":\"1767165249416\",\"hotelName\":\"Shillong\",\"destination\":\"Windermere Hotel or similar\",\"checkIn\":\"2026-03-04\",\"checkOut\":\"2026-03-07\",\"roomCategory\":\"Deluxe Room \",\"noOfRooms\":\"5\"},{\"key\":\"1767165250177\",\"hotelName\":\"Kaziranga National Park\",\"destination\":\"Royale De Casa Kaziranga or similar\",\"checkIn\":\"2026-03-07\",\"checkOut\":\"2026-03-09\",\"roomCategory\":\"Premier Room \",\"noOfRooms\":\"5\"},{\"key\":\"1767165251110\",\"hotelName\":\"Dirang\",\"destination\":\"Pemaling or similar\",\"checkIn\":\"2026-03-09\",\"checkOut\":\"2026-03-10\",\"roomCategory\":\"Club Room \",\"noOfRooms\":\"5\"},{\"key\":\"1767165251995\",\"hotelName\":\"Tawang\",\"destination\":\"Taktsang or similar\",\"checkIn\":\"2026-03-10\",\"checkOut\":\"2026-03-12\",\"roomCategory\":\"Executive Room \",\"noOfRooms\":\"5\"},{\"key\":\"1767165256809\",\"hotelName\":\"Bomdila\",\"destination\":\"Elysium or similar\",\"checkIn\":\"2026-03-12\",\"checkOut\":\"2026-03-13\",\"roomCategory\":\"Executive Room \",\"noOfRooms\":\"5\"}]}}'),
